commit.title: remove all traces of fedora 34
commit.message:
remove all traces of fedora 34

Fedora 34 is EOL, let's remove all traces of it, including:

- distro definition
- repositories (and test one)
- test manifests
- special package set rules
- hacks from the spec file

Signed-off-by: Ondřej Budai <ondrej@budai.cz>

user.name: Ondřej Budai
user.bio: Senior Software Engineer @ Image Builder, Red Hat

also test it there.
We also pin it for Fedora and RHEL/CS 9 to be able to use the
new `org.osbuild.containers.storage.conf` stage.

commit.title: image: introduce image kinds for Fedora
commit.message:
image: introduce image kinds for Fedora

Implement all of Fedora in terms of this new abstraction. What used to be the
manifest functions (and before that the pipeline functions) are now the image
functions, whose purpose is to instantiate the right image kind structs from the
image type definitions we currently have in the distro definition.

commit.title: image: introduce image kinds for Fedora
commit.message:
image: introduce image kinds for Fedora

Implement all of Fedora in terms of this new abstraction. What used to be the
manifest functions (and before that the pipeline functions) are now the image
functions, whose purpose is to instantiate the right image kind structs from the
image type definitions we currently have in the distro definition.
